154 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
155  while (false) { \
156  *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
157  }
158 
190 template <class T>
191 class Local {
192  public:
193  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
194  template <class S>
195  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
196  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
202  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
203  }
204 
208  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
209 
213  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
214 
215  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
216 
217  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
218 
229  template <class S>
230  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
231  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
232  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
233  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
234  if (b == nullptr) return false;
235  return *a == *b;
236  }
237 
238  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
239  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
240  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
241  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
242  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
243  if (b == nullptr) return false;
244  return *a == *b;
245  }
246 
257  template <class S>
258  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
259  return !operator==(that);
260  }
261 
262  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
263  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
264  return !operator==(that);
265  }
266 
272  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
273 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
274  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
275  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
276  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
277 #endif
278  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
279  }
280 
286  template <class S>
287  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
288  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
289  }
290 
296  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
297  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
298  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
299  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
300  const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
301 
302  private:
303  friend class Utils;
304  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
305  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
306  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
307  template<class F> friend class Local;
308  template <class F>
309  friend class MaybeLocal;
310  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
311  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
312  friend class String;
313  friend class Object;
314  friend class Context;
315  friend class Isolate;
316  friend class Private;
317  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
318  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
319  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
320  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
321  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
322  friend class HandleScope;
323  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
324  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
325  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
326  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
327  template <class F>
328  friend class ReturnValue;
329  template <class F>
330  friend class Traced;
331  template <class F>
332  friend class TracedGlobal;
333  template <class F>
334  friend class TracedReferenceBase;
335  template <class F>
336  friend class TracedReference;
337 
338  explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
339  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
340  T* val_;
341 };

371  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
372 
377  template <class S>
378  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
379  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
380  return !IsEmpty();
381  }
382

395  return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);

406 template <class T> class Eternal {
407  public:
408  V8_INLINE Eternal() : val_(nullptr) {}

411  Set(isolate, handle);
412  }
413  // Can only be safely called if already set.
414  V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const;
415  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }

423 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
424 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
425 
426 template <typename T>
427 class WeakCallbackInfo {
428  public:
429  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
430 
431  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
432  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
433  Callback* callback)
434  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
435  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
436  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
437  }
438  }
439 
440  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
441  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
442  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
443 
444  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451 
452  private:
453  Isolate* isolate_;
454  T* parameter_;
455  Callback* callback_;
456  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
457 };
458 
459 
460 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
461 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
462 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
463 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
464 // possible to request a second pass callback.
465 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
466

505  return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
506  }

511  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
512  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;

520  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
521  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
522  if (b == nullptr) return false;
523  return *a == *b;

605  friend class Object;

620 template<class T>
621 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
622  public:
623  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
624  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
625  template<class S, class M>
626  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
627  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
628  Uncompilable<Object>();
629  }
630  // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
631  template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
632  TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
633  }
634 };

661 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
662  public:
666  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
672  template <class S>
673  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
674  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
675  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
676  }
682  template <class S, class M2>
683  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
684  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
685  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
686  }
693  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
694  Copy(that);
695  }
696  template <class S, class M2>
697  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
698  Copy(that);
699  }
700  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
701  Copy(that);
702  return *this;
703  }
704  template <class S, class M2>
705  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
706  Copy(that);
707  return *this;
708  }
714  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
715  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
716  }
717 
718  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
719  template <class S>
720  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
721 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
722  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
723  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
724  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
725 #endif
726  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
727  }
728 
729  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
730  template <class S>
731  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
732  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
733  }
734 
735  private:
736  friend class Isolate;
737  friend class Utils;
738  template<class F> friend class Local;
739  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
740  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
741 
742  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
743  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
744  template<class S, class M2>
745  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
746 };

842 template <typename T>

844  public:
849  bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }

864  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
865  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
866  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
867  if (b == nullptr) return false;
868  return *a == *b;
869  }
870 
871  template <class S>
872  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
873  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
874  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
875  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
876  if (b == nullptr) return false;
877  return *a == *b;
878  }
879

882  return !operator==(that);
883  }
884

904  const_cast<TracedReferenceBase<T>&>(*this));
905  }
906 
907  private:

909 
913  TracedReferenceBase() = default;
914

916  DestructionMode destruction_mode);

1073 
1080  template <class S>
1081  TracedReference(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {
1082  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
1083  TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
1084  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
1085  }
1086 
1091  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference&& other) {
1092  // Forward to operator=.
1093  *this = std::move(other);
1094  }
1095 
1100  template <typename S>
1101  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference<S>&& other) {
1102  // Forward to operator=.
1103  *this = std::move(other);
1104  }
1105 
1110  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference& other) {
1111  // Forward to operator=;
1112  *this = other;
1113  }
1114 
1119  template <typename S>
1120  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference<S>& other) {
1121  // Forward to operator=;
1122  *this = other;
1123  }
1124 
1128  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1129 
1133  template <class S>
1134  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1135 
1139  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1140 
1144  template <class S>
1145  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1146 
1151  template <class S>
1152  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1153 
1154  template <class S>
1155  V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1156  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1157  const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1158  }
1159 };

1340 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1341  public:
1342  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1343  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1344  bool is_module = false)
1345  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1346  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1347  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1348  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1349  : flags_(flags &
1350  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1351 
1352  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1353  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1354  }
1355  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1356  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1357  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1358 
1359  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1360 
1361  private:
1362  enum {
1363  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1364  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1365  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1366  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1367  };
1368  const int flags_;
1369 };

1622 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1623  public:
1631  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1632  enum BufferPolicy {
1633  BufferNotOwned,
1634  BufferOwned
1635  };
1636 
1637  CachedData()
1638  : data(nullptr),
1639  length(0),
1640  rejected(false),
1641  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1642 
1643  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1644  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1645  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1646  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1647  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1648  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1649  ~CachedData();
1650  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1651  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1652  const uint8_t* data;
1653  int length;
1654  bool rejected;
1655  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1656 
1657  // Prevent copying.
1658  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1659  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1660  };

1676  // alive.
1677  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;

1680

3678  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3679  //
3680  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3681  // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3682  // or the object is not extensible.
3683  //

3692  // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3693  //
3694  // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3695  // for specifying attributes.
3696  //
3697  // Returns true on success.
3698  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineOwnProperty(
3699  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3700  PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3701 
3702  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3703  //
3704  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3705  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3706  //
3707  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3708  //
3709  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3710  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3711  //
3712  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3713  //
3714  // Returns true on success.
3715  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3716  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key,
3717  PropertyDescriptor& descriptor); // NOLINT(runtime/references)
3718

4213 template<typename T>
4214 class ReturnValue {
4215  public:
4216  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4217  : value_(that.value_) {
4218  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
4219  }
4220  // Local setters
4221  template <typename S>
4222  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4223  template <typename S>
4224  V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4225  template <typename S>
4226  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4227  // Fast primitive setters
4228  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4229  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4230  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4231  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4232  // Fast JS primitive setters
4233  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4234  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4235  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4236  // Convenience getter for Isolate
4237  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4238 
4239  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4240  template <typename S>
4241  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4242 
4243  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4244  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4245  // value.
4246  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4247 
4248  private:
4249  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4250  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4251  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4252  template <class F, class G, class H>
4253  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4254  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4255  V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4256  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4257  internal::Address* value_;
4258 };

6964 class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT
6965  public:
6966  // Note that the strings passed into this constructor must live as long
6967  // as the Extension itself.
6968  Extension(const char* name, const char* source = nullptr, int dep_count = 0,
6969  const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
6970  virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }
6971  virtual Local<FunctionTemplate> GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
6972  Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
6973  return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
6974  }
6975 
6976  const char* name() const { return name_; }
6977  size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
6978  const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
6979  return source_;
6980  }
6981  int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
6982  const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
6983  void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6984  bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6985 
6986  // Disallow copying and assigning.
6987  Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
6988  void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
6989 
6990  private:
6991  const char* name_;
6992  size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
6993  String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
6994  int dep_count_;
6995  const char** deps_;
6996  bool auto_enable_;
6997 };

7698 
7704 struct JitCodeEvent {
7705  enum EventType {
7706  CODE_ADDED,
7707  CODE_MOVED,
7708  CODE_REMOVED,
7709  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7710  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7711  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7712  };
7713  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7714  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7715  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7716  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7717  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7718  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7719 
7720  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7721  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7722  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7723  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7724  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7725  // function.
7726  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7727 
7728  // Type of event.
7729  EventType type;
7730  CodeType code_type;
7731  // Start of the instructions.
7732  void* code_start;
7733  // Size of the instructions.
7734  size_t code_len;
7735  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7736  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7737  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7738  // code line information which is returned from the
7739  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7740  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7741  void* user_data;
7742 
7743  struct name_t {
7744  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7745  // zero-terminated.
7746  const char* str;
7747  // Number of chars in str.
7748  size_t len;
7749  };
7750 
7751  struct line_info_t {
7752  // PC offset
7753  size_t offset;
7754  // Code position
7755  size_t pos;
7756  // The position type.
7757  PositionType position_type;
7758  };
7759 
7760  struct wasm_source_info_t {
7761  // Source file name.
7762  const char* filename;
7763  // Length of filename.
7764  size_t filename_size;
7765  // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7766  // source file.
7767  const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7768  // Number of entries in the line number table.
7769  size_t line_number_table_size;
7770  };
7771 
7772  wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7773 
7774  union {
7775  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7776  struct name_t name;
7777 
7778  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7779  struct line_info_t line_info;
7780 
7781  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7782  void* new_code_start;
7783  };
7784 
7785  Isolate* isolate;
7786 };
7787 
7793 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7794  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7795  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7796  // Throughput may be throttled.
7797  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7798  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7799  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7800  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7801  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7802  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7803  // in this mode.
7804  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7805  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7806  // turn off latency optimizations.
7807  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7808 };
7809

9882 
9893 template <class T>
9894 class Maybe {
9895  public:
9896  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9897  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9898 
9902  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9903 
9908  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9909  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9910  }
9911 
9916  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9917  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9918  return IsJust();
9919  }
9920 
9925  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9926  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9927  return value_;
9928  }
9929 
9934  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9935  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9936  }
9937 
9938  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9939  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9940  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9941  }
9942 
9943  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9944  return !operator==(other);
9945  }
9946 
9947  private:
9948  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9949  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9950 
9951  bool has_value_;
9952  T value_;
9953 
9954  template <class U>
9955  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9956  template <class U>
9957  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9958 };
9959 
9960 template <class T>
9961 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9962  return Maybe<T>();
9963 }
9964 
9965 template <class T>
9966 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
9967  return Maybe<T>(t);
9968 }
9969 
9970 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
9971 template <>
9972 class Maybe<void> {
9973  public:
9974  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
9975  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
9976 
9977  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9978  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
9979  }
9980 
9981  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9982  return !operator==(other);
9983  }
9984 
9985  private:
9986  struct JustTag {};
9987 
9988  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
9989  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
9990 
9991  bool is_valid_;
9992 
9993  template <class U>
9994  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9995  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
9996 };
9997 
9998 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10112  bool IsVerbose() const;
10113 
10119  void SetCaptureMessage(bool value);
10120 
10132  static void* JSStackComparableAddress(TryCatch* handler) {
10133  if (handler == nullptr) return nullptr;
10134  return handler->js_stack_comparable_address_;
10135  }
10136 
10137  TryCatch(const TryCatch&) = delete;
10138  void operator=(const TryCatch&) = delete;
10139 
10140  private:
10141  // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
10142  // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
10143  void* operator new(size_t size);
10144  void* operator new[](size_t size);
10145  void operator delete(void*, size_t);
10146  void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
10147 
10148  void ResetInternal();
10149 
10150  internal::Isolate* isolate_;
10151  TryCatch* next_;
10152  void* exception_;
10153  void* message_obj_;
10154  void* js_stack_comparable_address_;
10155  bool is_verbose_ : 1;
10156  bool can_continue_ : 1;
10157  bool capture_message_ : 1;
10158  bool rethrow_ : 1;
10159  bool has_terminated_ : 1;
10160 
10161  friend class internal::Isolate;
10162 };

10690 template <class T>
10691 Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10692  if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10693  T* that_ptr = that;
10694  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10695  return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10696  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10697 }

10739  V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10740  p));

10744 template <class T, class M>
10745 template <class S, class M2>
10746 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10747  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10748  this->Reset();
10749  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10750  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10751  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10752  M::Copy(that, this);
10753 }

10759  return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10760  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10761 }

10840 template <class T>
10841 Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
10842  if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
10843  V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10844  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10845  other.val_ = nullptr;
10846  }
10847 }
10848 
10849 template <class T>
10850 template <class S>
10851 Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10852  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10853  if (this != &rhs) {
10854  this->Reset();
10855  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10856  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10857  V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10858  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10859  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10860  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10861  }
10862  }
10863  return *this;
10864 }

10871  return reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
10872  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
10873  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
10874  destruction_mode == kWithDestructor));
10875 }

11050 template<typename T>
11051 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11052  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
11053  typedef internal::Internals I;
11054  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11055  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11056  return;
11057  }
11058  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11059 }
11060 
11061 template<typename T>
11062 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11063  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
11064  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11065  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11066  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11067  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11068  return;
11069  }
11070  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11071 }
11072 
11073 template<typename T>
11074 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11075  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
11076  typedef internal::Internals I;
11077  int root_index;
11078  if (value) {
11079  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11080  } else {
11081  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11082  }
11083  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11084 }
11085 
11086 template<typename T>
11087 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11088  TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
11089  typedef internal::Internals I;
11090  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11091 }
11092 
11093 template<typename T>
11094 void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11095  TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
11096  typedef internal::Internals I;
11097  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11098 }
11099 
11100 template<typename T>
11101 void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11102  TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
11103  typedef internal::Internals I;
11104  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11105 }
11106 
11107 template <typename T>
11108 Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11109  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11110  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11111 }

11113 template <typename T>
11114 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11115  typedef internal::Internals I;
11116  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11117  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11118  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11119 }

11121 template <typename T>
11122 template <typename S>
11123 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
11124  // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
11125  TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
11126 }
11127 
11128 template <typename T>
11129 internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11130  // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11131  return value_[-1];
11132 }

11134 template <typename T>
11135 FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::FunctionCallbackInfo(internal::Address* implicit_args,
11136  internal::Address* values,
11137  int length)
11138  : implicit_args_(implicit_args), values_(values), length_(length) {}
11139 
11140 template<typename T>
11141 Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11142  // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11143  if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11144 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11145  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));
11146 #else
11147  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
11148 #endif
11149 }

11152 template<typename T>

11154  // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11155 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11156  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ - 1));
11157 #else
11158  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
11159 #endif
11160 }

11313 
11314 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11315 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11316  typedef internal::Address A;
11317  typedef internal::Internals I;
11318  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11319  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11320  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11321  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11322  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11323  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11324  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11325  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11326  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11327 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11328  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11329  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11330  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11331 #endif
11332  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11333  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11334  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11335  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11336  }
11337 #endif
11338  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11339 }
11340 
11341 
11342 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11343 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11344  typedef internal::Address A;
11345  typedef internal::Internals I;
11346  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11347  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11348  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11349  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11350  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11351  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11352  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11353  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11354  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
11355  }
11356 #endif
11357  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11358 }

11368 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {

11370  typedef internal::Internals I;

11373  return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11374 }

11376 
11377 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11378  typedef internal::Address A;
11379  typedef internal::Internals I;
11380  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11381 
11382  ExternalStringResource* result;
11383  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11384  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11385  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11386  } else {
11387  result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11388  }
11389 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11390  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11391 #endif
11392  return result;
11393 }
11394 
11395 
11396 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11397  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11398  typedef internal::Address A;
11399  typedef internal::Internals I;
11400  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11401  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11402  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11403  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11404  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11405  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11406  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11407  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11408  } else {
11409  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11410  }
11411 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11412  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11413 #endif
11414  return resource;
11415 }

11426 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11427  typedef internal::Address A;
11428  typedef internal::Internals I;
11429  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11430  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11431  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11432  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11433 }

11460 
11461 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11462  typedef internal::Address A;
11463  typedef internal::Internals I;
11464  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11465  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11466  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11467  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11468  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11469 }

11919 
11920 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11921  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11922  typedef internal::Internals I;
11923  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
11924  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11925  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11926  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11927  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11928  int64_t* external_memory_low_since_mc =
11929  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11930  I::kExternalMemoryLowSinceMarkCompactOffset);
11931 
11932  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11933  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11934  const int64_t amount =
11935  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11936  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11937  *external_memory = amount;
11938 
11939  if (amount < *external_memory_low_since_mc) {
11940  *external_memory_low_since_mc = amount;
11941  *external_memory_limit = amount + I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit;
11942  }
11943 
11944  if (change_in_bytes <= 0) return *external_memory;
11945 
11946  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc = static_cast<int64_t>(
11947  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
11948  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_low_since_mc));
11949  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
11950  // external memory increased.
11951  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
11952  CheckMemoryPressure();
11953  }
11954  if (amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11955  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11956  }
11957  return *external_memory;
11958 }
11959 
11960 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11961 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11962  typedef internal::Address A;
11963  typedef internal::Internals I;
11964  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11965  A embedder_data =
11966  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11967  int value_offset =
11968  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11969  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11970 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11971  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11972  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11973  value =
11974  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11975 #endif
11976  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
11977  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
11978  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11979  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11980 #else
11981  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
11982 #endif
11983 }
11984 
11985 
11986 void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
11987 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11988  typedef internal::Address A;
11989  typedef internal::Internals I;
11990  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11991  A embedder_data =
11992  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11993  int value_offset =
11994  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11995  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11996 #else
11997  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
11998 #endif
11999 }
